      <div class="pfd1-faq__list">
        <details class="pfd1-faq__item">
          <summary>How is WLP-1 different from GLP-1 injections?</summary>
          <p>WLP-1 is a daily oral supplement, not a prescription drug. It supports the body's own natural GLP-1 signaling pathway using clinically studied botanical ingredients<sup>*</sup>, which means no needles, no prescription, and no scheduled side effects. GLP-1 injections work on a single pathway. WLP-1 supports three: appetite, metabolism, and thermogenesis.<sup>*</sup></p>
        </details>
        <details class="pfd1-faq__item">
          <summary>Are there side effects?</summary>
          <p>WLP-1 is formulated with food-derived botanicals (Irvingia gabonensis, CQR300, Grains of Paradise) and is safe for consistent daily use. Most customers report no side effects. As with any supplement, talk to your doctor before starting if you are pregnant, nursing, or on prescription medication.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="pfd1-faq__item">
          <summary>When do I see results?</summary>
          <p>Most customers notice reduced cravings and a quieter appetite within the first one to two weeks. Visible body composition changes typically appear at the four-week mark, in line with clinical research on the active ingredients (~9 lbs in 4 weeks on average<sup>*</sup>).</p>
        </details>
        <details class="pfd1-faq__item">
          <summary>What is actually in it?</summary>
          <p>Three clinically studied actives: <b>IGOB131</b> (Irvingia gabonensis), <b>CQR300</b>, and <b>Grains of Paradise</b>. All delivered in our absorption-enhanced format, which our internal testing shows can deliver up to <b>20x more absorption</b> than standard supplement formats. Made in the USA, third-party tested.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="pfd1-faq__item">
          <summary>Is there a money-back guarantee?</summary>
          <p>Every WLP-1 order is backed by a <b>30-day money-back guarantee</b>. If you are not satisfied for any reason, email us within 30 days of delivery and we will refund your order.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="pfd1-faq__item">
          <summary>Can I take WLP-1 alongside GLP-1 injections?</summary>
          <p>Many customers use WLP-1 to support and extend the effects of a GLP-1 injection regimen, since WLP-1 is working through complementary metabolic pathways.<sup>*</sup> Talk to your prescribing physician before combining.</p>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============ FINAL CTA ============ -->
  <section class="pfd1-close">
    <div class="wrap">
      <p class="pfd1-close__kicker">Last apology</p>
      <h2>You have been <em>warned</em>.</h2>
      <p>If new pants, longer workouts, and a quieter snack drawer sound like problems you can live with, WLP-1 is two pills a day, no prescription, no needles. Most customers start with the 3-month plan, because that is when the second- and third-month changes really start showing up in the mirror.</p>
      <a href="#buy">Get WLP-1</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============ DISCLAIMER ============ -->
  <div class="pfd1-disclaim">
    <div class="wrap">
      <p><sup>*</sup> These statements have not been evaluated by the Food and Drug Administration. This product is not intended to diagnose, treat, cure, or prevent any disease. Individual results vary. Clinical results referenced are from independent published studies on the active botanical ingredients (Irvingia gabonensis, CQR300, Grains of Paradise) used in WLP-1, not on the finished product. Weight loss figures are averages from those studies and are not guaranteed.</p>
      <p>WLP-1 is not a GLP-1 receptor agonist drug and is not a substitute for prescription medication. Talk to your healthcare provider before starting any new supplement, particularly if you are pregnant, nursing, or taking prescription medication.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

